un’. It has sometimes been taken as connected with the Greek word meaning ‘Greek’, <i>Hellēn</i>, but this is doubtful. In the early Christian period the name was borne by the mother of the Emperor Constantine, who is now usually known by the Latin version of her name, <i>Helena</i>. She is credited with having found the True Cross in Jerusalem. She was born in about  248 , probably in Bithynia. However, in medieval England it was believed that she had been born in Britain, which greatly increased the popularity of the name there."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Helen Kynaston was born about 1480. She married Thomas Kynaston of Estwick in Shropshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1480–":"umbes 1480–Surnud","1470–1529":"1470–1529","1499–1549":"1499–1549","1517–1568":"1517–1568","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","about 1480":"umbes 1480","1568":"1568","1499":"1499","abt 1517":"umbes 1517","about 1499":"umbes 1499","1470":"1470","1480":"1480","1529":"1529","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"about 1480–":"noin 1480–Kuollut","1470–1529":"1470–1529","1499–1549":"1499–1549","1517–1568":"1517–1568","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","about 1480":"noin 1480","1568":"1568","1499":"1499","abt 1517":"noin 1517","about 1499":"noin 1499","1470":"1470","1480":"1480","1529":"1529","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fr":{"about 1480–":"environ 1480–Décédée","1470–1529":"1470–1529","1499–1549":"1499–1549","1517–1568":"1517–1568","1480–Female":"1480–Décédée","about 1480":"environ 1480","1568":"1568","1499":"1499","abt 1517":"environ 1517","about 1499":"environ 1499","1470":"1470","1480":"1480","1529":"1529","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre","Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Helen Kynaston est née environ 1480. Elle a épousé Thomas Kynaston